 {"id":"frankenpandas-ijpu","title":"fp-conformance: phase2c_artifact_test_lock poison-tolerance (18 test cascade)","description":"Observed: cargo test -p fp-conformance --lib reports 18 FAILED / 334 passed with every failure message 'phase2c artifact test lock poisoned: PoisonError { .. }'.\n\nRoot: crates/fp-conformance/src/lib.rs:20181 phase2c_artifact_test_lock uses std::sync::Mutex and expect() on a poisoned lock. Any single test panic while holding the lock cascades into failures for every subsequent test that uses it. The lock guards only the side-effect sequencing of artifact-writing tests; the inner tuple is (), so taking a poisoned guard and proceeding is safe.\n\nFix: replace .expect() with .unwrap_or_else(|err| err.into_inner()) to recover the guard through the poison. Downstream call sites don't need changes. \nTests: cargo test -p fp-conformance --lib should go from 334/18 → 352/0 (or reveal the underlying panic buried by the cascade).","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2026-04-22T04:29:48.729395236Z","created_by":"ubuntu","updated_at":"2026-04-22T04:35:16.486344833Z","closed_at":"2026-04-22T04:35:16.483797039Z","close_reason":"shipped 2c98ff2: phase2c_artifact_test_lock now recovers poisoned guards via into_inner() (safe because inner is ()). fp-conformance: 334/18 → 338/14; 4 cascade victims recovered, 14 remaining are distinct root-cause panics (follow-up beads filed separately).","source_repo":".","compaction_level":0,"original_size":0}
